{"body": ">Another solution to this problem is to add a note to the regular index on development showing it is only available in development.\r\n\r\nYes, we can add a simple conditional, `unless Rails.env.development`  & then only render [this line](https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/master/railties/lib/rails/templates/rails/welcome/index.html.erb#L214). Else it would a normal static page with no info", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21343409", "created_at": "2013-07-22T13:25:30Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11514#issuecomment-21343409", "updated_at": "2013-07-22T13:26:46Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11514, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/gaurish", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/cb0b42e452cd13d469565a23a8abe441?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F58861ae4fb7b472c95e64685229ad9ed.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/received_events", "gravatar_id": "cb0b42e452cd13d469565a23a8abe441", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "gaurish", "type": "User", "id": 235844, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/gaurish/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d3a8bd3543c151007fc7"}, "id": 21343409, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11514"}
